# Production operations

Use this module when the application serves users or runs as an operated service.

Record the accountable owner, service health signal, operating limits, observability source, release and
rollback procedure, incident path, data dependencies, and model-provider dependencies. A health check should
answer an operational question rather than expose internals or trigger expensive model calls.

Define what happens when inference is slow, unavailable, over budget, or returns invalid output. Link
release claims and incidents to evidence and decisions.

This module documents operating responsibilities. It does not deploy infrastructure, configure monitoring,
or make the application production-ready by itself.
